section.section:
This section does not apply to:
The purchase of books or other materials for instruction;
Emergency repairs;
Any contract or purchase made by a county for a community college under procedures authorized by the county charter or an act of the General Assembly; or
Any contract or purchase that qualifies as a "small procurement" as defined in the State Procurement Regulations.

Except as provided in subsection (f) of this section, the contract shall be awarded to the lowest responsible bidder, who conforms to the specifications, with consideration given to:
The quantities involved;
The time required for delivery;
The purpose for which required;
The competence and responsibility of the bidder; and
The ability of the bidder to perform the contract satisfactorily.
